Topping: Combine oats, flour, and sugar in medium bowl. Using pastry cutter, or 2 knives, cut in butter until mixture is crumbly. Stir in Shreddies until combined. Set aside. Filling: Combine pear and cranberries in large bowl. Stir in remaining ingredients. Transfer mixture to lightly greased 9-inch (23 cm) square baking dish. Sprinkle topping over fruit. Bake at 350 degrees F (180 degrees C) for 35 to 40 min. or until fruit is tender, and topping is golden.